gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Lakers 141, Bulls 132
gameRecap.excerpt: The Lakers defeated the Bulls, 141-132. DAngelo Russell recorded 29 points and a season-high eight 3PM for the Lakers, while LeBron James (25 points, 12 assists) and Anthony Davis (22 points, 11 rebounds, six assists) combined for 47 points in the victory. DeMar DeRozan tallied 32 points and 10 assists for the Bulls in the losing effort. The Lakers improve to 23-23 on the season, while the Bulls fall to 21-25.
